# Technology Rules (Maverick)

Repository-specific technology standards. Subordinate to `20-project-conventions.mdc`.

## Next.js 15 App Router

- Single route: `app/page.tsx` composes sections (server component)
- Root layout: fonts, metadata, skip link in `app/layout.tsx`
- **Server:** `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, static presentational components
- **Client:** `"use client"` first line for interactive UI (nav, sections, video)
- New sections → `app/sections/` + barrel + `page.tsx`
- New components → `app/components/` + barrel
- Cross-folder imports: `@/` alias
- **No API routes** unless explicitly requested
- **No global state** — local hooks only

## Signal Slate Design System

Sources: `app/globals.css`, `tailwind.config.ts`, `lib/utils.ts`

**Prefer:**
- Semantic tokens: `bg-surface`, `text-ink-muted`, `text-accent-deep`
- Component classes: `.container-wide`, `.section`, `.btn-primary`, `.section-tag`, `.cap-card`
- `cn()` for class merging
- 8px grid: `grid-*` spacing

**Avoid:** Hardcoded hex when semantic token exists; duplicate layout inline

## Framer Motion

- Use Framer's `useInView(ref, { once: true, margin: "-15%" })` in sections
- Easing: `[0.16, 1, 0.3, 1]`
- Hero: mount animations; sections: scroll reveals
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` (globals.css + `HeroVideoBackground.tsx`)

## Section Contracts

| Section | `id` | Nav hash |
|---------|------|----------|
| Hero | `hero` | `#hero` |
| Founders | `founders` | `#founders` |
| Services | `services` | `#services` |
| Contact | `contact` | `#contact` |

Every section: `anchor` class from `@/lib/utils`. Update nav + barrel + `page.tsx` together.

## Accessibility

- Skip link → `#main-content`
- `aria-label` on icon-only buttons
- `aria-hidden="true"` on decorative SVGs/video
- `prefers-reduced-motion` support required

## Deploy (Vercel)

- Semver Git tags per `docs/VERSIONING.md`
- Rollback via tag checkout or Vercel promote
- Never force-push `main`
- Do not deploy unless explicitly requested

## Validation

After technology-layer changes: `npm run build` + `npx tsc --noEmit` + relevant smoke checks.
